headline: Lockheed Martin clinches $4.94 billion US Army missile contract
summary: Defense companies are seeing a surge in weaponry demand, driven by conflicts across the globe.  The Pentagon has been prioritizing purchases of the PrSM, which is to replace the Army Tactical Missile (ATACM).  PrSM is Lockheed's next-generation long-range precision strike missile, capable of neutralizing targets beyond 400 kilometers.
